## Gate 3 — OWASP Top 10 Verification

Test the live staging application against the OWASP Top 10 web application risks.

For each risk, test and record the result:

| # | Risk | Test | Result |
|---|------|------|--------|
| A01 | Broken Access Control | Access another user's resources with a valid but different user's token | Pass / Fail |
| A02 | Cryptographic Failures | Check HTTPS enforced; no sensitive data in URLs or logs; passwords hashed | Pass / Fail |
| A03 | Injection | Submit SQL/NoSQL injection payloads in all text inputs and query params | Pass / Fail |
| A04 | Insecure Design | Review auth flows and business logic for design-level flaws | Pass / Fail |
| A05 | Security Misconfiguration | Check default credentials, verbose error messages, directory listing, debug mode off | Pass / Fail |
| A06 | Vulnerable Components | Covered by Gate 1 | Pass / Fail |
| A07 | Authentication Failures | Brute force attempt; check rate limiting fires; check account lockout | Pass / Fail |
| A08 | Software & Data Integrity | Verify CI/CD pipeline cannot be tampered with; check subresource integrity on CDN assets | Pass / Fail |
| A09 | Logging Failures | Confirm auth events, errors, and admin actions are logged; confirm logs don't contain passwords | Pass / Fail |
| A10 | SSRF | If app fetches external URLs (e.g. webhooks, link previews), test for SSRF with internal IP targets | Pass / Fail / N/A |

For each Fail, file a finding:
```
SEC-[NNN]: [Short title]
OWASP Category: A0N — [name]
Severity: Critical | High | Medium | Low
Description: [what the vulnerability is]
Reproduction: [steps to reproduce]
Impact: [what an attacker could do]
Recommendation: [specific fix]
```

**Output block:**
```
GATE 3 STATUS: APPROVED | REVISION NEEDED
OWASP findings: [count]
Critical/High findings: [count — must be 0 to proceed]
```

