## Gate 4 — HTTP Security Headers Audit

Test the live staging URL for correct HTTP security headers.

Run:
```bash
curl -I https://[staging-url]/api/health
curl -I https://[staging-frontend-url]
```

Or use: https://securityheaders.com (grade A or above required)

Required headers:

| Header | Required Value | Fail condition |
|--------|----------------|----------------|
| `Strict-Transport-Security` | `max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains` | Missing or max-age < 1 year |
| `X-Frame-Options` | `DENY` or `SAMEORIGIN` | Missing |
| `X-Content-Type-Options` | `nosniff` | Missing |
| `Referrer-Policy` | `strict-origin-when-cross-origin` or stricter | Missing |
| `Content-Security-Policy` | Defined (not `unsafe-inline` without nonce/hash for scripts) | Missing entirely |
| `Permissions-Policy` | Defined | Missing (medium severity) |
| `Access-Control-Allow-Origin` | Specific origin(s) — NOT `*` on production API | `*` is a fail for authenticated APIs |

Forbidden response headers (expose server information):
- `X-Powered-By` — must be removed
- `Server` — should be removed or obscured

**Output block:**
```
GATE 4 STATUS: APPROVED | REVISION NEEDED
Security headers score: [A+ / A / B / C / F]
Missing required headers: [list — must be empty to proceed]
```

