## Gate 5 — Authentication & Session Security

Test the authentication system end-to-end on staging:

**Token security:**
- [ ] JWT tokens have a sensible expiry (access token ≤ 1 hour, refresh token ≤ 30 days)
- [ ] JWT algorithm is RS256 or HS256 with a strong secret — not `none` or `HS256` with a weak secret
- [ ] Refresh tokens are stored in httpOnly, Secure, SameSite=Strict cookies — not in localStorage
- [ ] Access tokens are NOT stored in localStorage (vulnerable to XSS)

**Session lifecycle:**
- [ ] Login creates a new session token (not reuses an old one)
- [ ] Logout invalidates the refresh token server-side (token blacklist or short expiry + rotation)
- [ ] Password reset invalidates all existing sessions
- [ ] Concurrent session handling matches the spec (allow multiple / single session per user)

**Password policy (if email+password auth):**
- [ ] Minimum 8 characters enforced
- [ ] Common passwords rejected (check against Have I Been Pwned API or a blocklist)
- [ ] Password reset tokens expire within 1 hour and are single-use
- [ ] No password is ever logged, returned in a response, or stored in plaintext

**Rate limiting verified on staging:**
- [ ] Login: max 5 attempts per 15 min per IP → 429 response
- [ ] Password reset: max 3 requests per hour per email
- [ ] Registration: max 10 per hour per IP

**Output block:**
```
GATE 5 STATUS: APPROVED | REVISION NEEDED
Auth findings: [count]
```

