## Gate 6 — Data Privacy & Compliance

Assess compliance requirements from `docs/product-brief.md`:

**All projects (baseline):**
- [ ] Passwords are hashed (bcrypt / argon2) — never stored plaintext
- [ ] PII (names, emails, phone numbers) is not logged in plaintext in application logs
- [ ] Database backups are encrypted at rest
- [ ] Database connection uses TLS
- [ ] File uploads (if any) are not accessible without authentication

**GDPR (if applicable):**
- [ ] Privacy policy page exists and is linked from the app
- [ ] Cookie consent banner implemented (if using non-essential cookies/tracking)
- [ ] User can request their data export (or a plan for this is documented)
- [ ] User can request account deletion (or a plan is documented)
- [ ] Data processing is limited to what is necessary for the stated purpose
- [ ] Third-party services (analytics, email) are disclosed in the privacy policy

**HIPAA (if applicable):**
- [ ] PHI is encrypted at rest and in transit
- [ ] Access to PHI is logged with user ID and timestamp
- [ ] BAA (Business Associate Agreement) is in place with all vendors handling PHI
- [ ] Minimum necessary access principle applied to all data queries

**SOC 2 (if applicable):**
- [ ] Access controls documented
- [ ] Audit log of admin actions retained for minimum 1 year
- [ ] Incident response plan documented
- [ ] Change management process in place (PRs, reviews, CI/CD)

For each failed check, file a finding with severity.

**Output block:**
```
GATE 6 STATUS: APPROVED | REVISION NEEDED
Compliance scope: [GDPR / HIPAA / SOC 2 / baseline only]
Compliance gaps: [count — critical gaps must be 0 to proceed]
```

---

## Gate 7 — Infrastructure Security Review

Review the deployed infrastructure configuration:

- [ ] All services run with least-privilege IAM roles (no wildcard `*` permissions in production)
- [ ] Database is not publicly accessible — only reachable from the application server
- [ ] Admin panels / internal tools are IP-restricted or behind VPN
- [ ] SSH access to servers (if applicable) uses key-based auth only, not passwords
- [ ] Object storage buckets (S3, GCS) are not publicly readable unless intentionally serving public assets
- [ ] Public assets in object storage do not include any user-uploaded files with PII
- [ ] Unused ports are closed — only 80/443 (and 22 if needed) open to the internet
- [ ] Automatic security updates enabled on the underlying OS (if applicable)
- [ ] Staging environment cannot access production database or secrets

**Output block:**
```
GATE 7 STATUS: APPROVED | REVISION NEEDED
Infrastructure findings: [count]
Critical infrastructure issues: [count — must be 0]
```

---

## Gate 8 — Finding Resolution & Sign-off

Collect all findings from Gates 1–7. For each:

```
SEC-[NNN]: [Title]
Gate: [1–7]
Severity: Critical | High | Medium | Low
Status: OPEN | RESOLVED | ACCEPTED (with justification)
Fix owner: Frontend | Backend | DevOps
Resolution: [what was changed or why accepted]
```

**Resolution thresholds to proceed:**
- All Critical and High findings: RESOLVED or ACCEPTED with written justification signed off by user
- Medium findings: RESOLVED or ACCEPTED with justification
- Low findings: logged, not blocking

Present all open findings to the user. For any finding the user wishes to accept rather than fix, record the justification explicitly.

**Output block:**
```
GATE 8 STATUS: APPROVED | REVISION NEEDED
Critical/High findings: [count resolved / total]
Medium findings: [count resolved / total]
Accepted risk items: [count]
```

